# Load necessary libraries
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(forecast)
library(lubridate)
library(xgboost)
library(caret)
library(tidyr)
library(zoo)  


data <- read.csv("IWC_Work_Orders_Extract.csv")
# Filter the data and summarize daily downtime per location
filtered_df <- data %>%
  filter(FUNCTIONAL_AREA_NODE_4_MODIFIED == "FILLER") %>%
  mutate(date = as.Date(EXECUTION_START_DATE)) %>%
  filter(month(EXECUTION_START_DATE) == 1, year(EXECUTION_START_DATE) == 2024)

downtime_per_day <- filtered_df %>%
  group_by(date, PRODUCTION_LOCATION) %>%
  summarise(total_downtime = sum(ACTUAL_WORK_IN_MINUTES, na.rm = TRUE))

# Plot downtime per day by production location
ggplot(downtime_per_day, aes(x = date, y = total_downtime, fill = PRODUCTION_LOCATION)) +
  geom_col() +
  labs(title = "Daily Downtime of FILLER in January 2024",
       x = "Date",
       y = "Total Downtime (in Minutes)",
       fill = "Production Location") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

# Select a specific location to model
location_data <- downtime_per_day %>%
  filter(PRODUCTION_LOCATION == "COTA") %>% # Change "Location_A" to actual location names
  arrange(date)

# Create a time series object for total downtime
downtime_ts <- ts(location_data$total_downtime, start = c(2024, 1), frequency = 30)

# Fit an ARIMA model to the time series data
arima_model <- auto.arima(downtime_ts)

# Print the model summary
summary(arima_model)
## Series: downtime_ts 
## ARIMA(0,0,1) with non-zero mean 
## 
## Coefficients:
##          ma1     mean
##       0.3386  571.669
## s.e.  0.1609   88.586
## 
## sigma^2 = 143133:  log likelihood = -219.67

# Forecast downtime for the next 7 days
forecasted_downtime <- forecast(arima_model, h = 7)

# Plot forecasted values
autoplot(forecasted_downtime) +
  labs(title = "Forecasted Downtime for FILLER - Location_A",
       x = "Date",
       y = "Total Downtime (in Minutes)")

# Load necessary libraries
library(ggplot2)
library(xgboost)
library(dplyr)
library(caret)  # For createDataPartition
library(zoo)    # If you're using zoo objects

# 1. Data Preparation (assuming you have filtered_df ready)
# Filter data for each production location
filtered_df <- data %>%
  dplyr::filter(FUNCTIONAL_AREA_NODE_4_MODIFIED == "FILLER") %>%
  mutate(date = as.Date(EXECUTION_START_DATE)) %>%
  dplyr::filter(month(EXECUTION_START_DATE) == 1, year(EXECUTION_START_DATE) == 2024)

# Summarize the total downtime per day
downtime_per_day <- filtered_df %>%
  group_by(date, PRODUCTION_LOCATION) %>%
  summarise(total_downtime = sum(ACTUAL_WORK_IN_MINUTES, na.rm = TRUE))

# Convert the data into a wide format if you have multiple locations
downtime_wide <- downtime_per_day %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = PRODUCTION_LOCATION, values_from = total_downtime, values_fill = list(total_downtime = 0))

# Assuming you're interested in just one production location for simplicity
location_data <- downtime_wide %>% select(date, COTA)  # Replace FILLER with your actual location column name
location_data <- location_data %>% mutate(FILLER = as.numeric(COTA))

# 2. Prepare training and testing datasets
set.seed(123)  # For reproducibility
train_index <- createDataPartition(location_data$FILLER, p = 0.8, list = FALSE)
train_data <- location_data[train_index, ]
test_data <- location_data[-train_index, ]

# 3. Prepare data for XGBoost
dtrain <- xgb.DMatrix(data = as.matrix(train_data[,-1]), label = train_data$FILLER)  # Exclude the date column
dtest <- xgb.DMatrix(data = as.matrix(test_data[,-1]), label = test_data$FILLER)

# 4. Train the XGBoost model
params <- list(
  objective = "reg:squarederror",
  eval_metric = "rmse"
)

model <- xgb.train(params = params, 
                   data = dtrain, 
                   nrounds = 100)

# 5. Make predictions
predictions <- predict(model, dtest)

# 6. Visualize feature importance
importance_matrix <- xgb.importance(model = model)
xgb.plot.importance(importance_matrix)

# 7. Predicted vs Actual values
actuals <- test_data$FILLER  # Replace with your actual test target

# Create a data frame for plotting
results <- data.frame(Actual = actuals, Predicted = predictions)

# Predicted vs Actual visualization
ggplot(results, aes(x = Actual, y = Predicted)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_abline(slope = 1, intercept = 0, color = 'red', linetype = 'dashed') +
  labs(title = "Predicted vs Actual Downtime",
       x = "Actual Downtime",
       y = "Predicted Downtime") +
  theme_minimal()

# 8. Calculate the errors
results$error <- results$Actual - results$Predicted

# Error Distribution visualization
ggplot(results, aes(x = error)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 30, fill = 'blue', alpha = 0.7) +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Prediction Errors",
       x = "Error (Actual - Predicted)",
       y = "Frequency") +
  theme_minimal()

# 9. Time Series Plot
results$date <- test_data$date  # Replace with your actual date column

ggplot(results, aes(x = date)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = Actual, color = "Actual"), size = 1) +
  geom_line(aes(y = Predicted, color = "Predicted"), size = 1) +
  labs(title = "Actual vs Predicted Downtime Over Time",
       x = "Date",
       y = "Downtime") +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Actual" = "blue", "Predicted" = "orange")) +
  theme_minimal()
